truth:
Pre-seeded environment (before the agent runs):

1. Paths & permissions
   • Directory /home/user/data already exists with default user writable permissions (0755).
   • Directory /home/user/report does NOT yet exist.
   • The agent runs as user “user”, so it can create /home/user/report.

2. File: /home/user/data/inventory.json
Exact content (including newlines and spaces):
{
  "warehouse": "central",
  "items": [
    {"id":101,"name":"blue widget","quantity":5},
    {"id":102,"name":"red widget","quantity":25},
    {"id":203,"name":"green gizmo","quantity":7},
    {"id":304,"name":"yellow gizmo","quantity":12}
  ]
}

3. File: /home/user/data/inventory_schema.json  
Not actually used by the grader but present for realism; exact content:
{
  "$schema":"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type":"object",
  "required":["warehouse","items"],
  "properties":{
    "warehouse":{"type":"string"},
    "items":{
      "type":"array",
      "items":{
        "type":"object",
        "required":["id","name","quantity"],
        "properties":{
          "id":{"type":"integer"},
          "name":{"type":"string"},
          "quantity":{"type":"integer","minimum":0}
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

Expected artefact after successful agent action:

1. Directory /home/user/report exists (0755 default directory perms).
2. File /home/user/report/low_stock_report.json  
   Exact expected content (including the single trailing newline character):
[101,203]

(That is left bracket, 101, comma, 203, right bracket, newline.)

The grader will:
• Confirm the file exists.
• Read its bytes and compare them verbatim with “[101,203]\n”.
   Any extra character, whitespace, or missing newline will fail the check.
